{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> καρπ-ίζω</b> <br /> <br /><Level1><b>__A</b></Level1>, (καρπός A) <b>enjoy the fruits of,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Inscriptiones Graecae 12(5).243 (from Paros)\">Refs</a>]:— elsewhere always in <i>middle</i>, κ. γῆν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Theopompus Historicus 217b; κλῆρον “PFrankf.” 7.7 (3rd c.BC),compare 4th c.BC: Hyperides Orator “Fragmenta” 119, LXX.Josh.5.12, “IG” 5(2).419.14 (Phigalea, 3rd c.BC), [prev. work]7.413.28, +others (Oropus, 1st c.BC)\">LXX+4th c.BC+</a>], etc.; Χρόνον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 3p.61U. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; but also, <b>exhaust</b> the soil, καρπίζεται τὴν γῆν μάλιστα πυρός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 8.9.1, compare “CP” 4.8.1: _metaphorically_, δόξαν ἐσθλήν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 432; κῦδος ἐκαρπίσατο “epigram Gr.” 516.4 (from Aegae), compare “Supp.epigram” 3.781 (from Gortyn)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>exploit</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “BGU” 1571 (1st c.AD)\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; βέλτιον ἐμὲ (i.e. τὴν σοφίαν) καρπίζεσθαι ὑπὲρ Χρυσίον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Pro.8.19. \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__A.II</b></Level2> <b>make fruitful, fertilize</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 408 (Lyric poetry), “Hel.” 1328 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7801","accentedUnicode":"καρπίζω","shortDef":"to gather fruit","mediumDef":"to gather fruit","stepGloss":"to gather fruit","stepTransliteration":"karpizō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}